**SUSTAINABLE TECHNOLOGY ADOPTION SCORE: 72/100**

Technology Adoption: 18/25  
Innovation Leadership: 16/25  
Measurable Impact: 18/25  
Future Strategy: 12/15  
Industry Position: 8/10

Summary judgment (one line): L3Harris is a strong, fast-moving adopter of operational sustainable technologies (large VPPAs, on‑site solar, major water‑reuse and facility efficiency projects) with credible mid-term targets (2030) and measurable early wins — it ranks among the better performers in aerospace & defense but is not clearly the sector’s single innovation leader in proprietary low‑carbon technologies or sustainable‑tech IP.

Findings and evidence (2022–2025 examples; citations provided):

Key Technologies Adopted (what they have implemented) — evidence and examples
- Large-scale renewable energy procurement: a virtual power purchase agreement (VPPA) tied to the Elm Branch Solar Farm (Lightsource BP) that L3Harris estimates will avoid roughly 110,000 metric tons CO2e per year (a material contribution to its enterprise energy mix). This VPPA and other renewables support the company’s commitment to source 40% of electricity from renewables by 2030 [lightsourcebp](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQG9jVt-0UjBDO3tlVPj7Xnu73_r_4ouBGo5NOowdPnCQ40H658dG69oIci0e4FmPB8oFMyl1Kny2j34pHc0cnC8Kl84egu06pZ0n0MBows9S_HLyPZgslam1wRxCNR84FKuzM52yCu53pIxfY7R4p08VqtWQd4imglYfzlfx20A) [esgtoday](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFbcvVWFs-xlqjlF1i1Axw3meBw8OeVdCeDXn9IdSk5WXqJLIC8WSVanJr_K6VjQbfaAnDEHO1nYXSuST5P0vy2-aeSB8uwuTiQrEP1SO8mBwXpbFqpn8ng5p-x5vjNK0QelZBhBTjJkBJP7eIO9DPGeURwOmW0NJOLIZ_ToCcFp2c=) [responsibilityreports](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHg0bkQEw71u5Qhh3TZ8LmpZFRlFVwWKpUsTVX4TrSh-U4xAn8TiRL-Q_VmlV-BKgAbtdoRgKSMTH4Ztgzki8WGNT9RLl92dTsOFOjfNqN1Z2iliP0ei6jg_UC1_dcYmfrBc7vKkpulrUi-23kH9Rl-H8s0CYsSYtn9CFWkSigcY4jHWhOc-y7AHKSg9axCNoqe4HNIvPZa-QFA) [smartenergydecisions](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGOMWGfk4WQawhkp4JBEYXT6LD5Pz5RqSPtfRMc3l1ryQNDc3ckZsQoSRQ41sDAvrVLgHyx-eMy6lD0MBIVgls6NEG9yhqPz2HrvnEvP99an3JRgu3KaTYTy2KXdeqC4nM-v3ktA_gQhCekLVtbSr48p3rrOleNv-GO-C3tqfWFgV6316__yo-dEBrWDE3ykgKpfsA=).
- On‑site solar: a planned/under‑construction San Diego solar carport intended to supply ~95% of that site’s electricity demand (scheduled operational end of 2025) and additional negotiated projects (2023–2025 pipeline) [l3harris](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQH_36jhGaMHdE_B8-4-qwt0QJxca51Y9Odl0QXZoFLTqM7cza5iZzUwESRchzujXvmlEal5IFz-6zXnKz4ZbuH6Bmg9puDEG1zOhd5WlOiC3SbYhkpMTWqZwcY4SdYCKigwzLohkF-W0ffFYM4leql_6sWK0E-yiE4Cayjj1gcZ3gUbOgKasKosfSSPS0wI4jCbGzE1hDyUPxgHNDoHB2NbPzqCGPBeqJD0uX7SdpRD3BPsaQ==) [responsibilityreports](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHg0bkQEw71u5Qhh3TZ8LmpZFRlFVwWKpUsTVX4TrSh-U4xAn8TiRL-Q_VmlV-BKgAbtdoRgKSMTH4Ztgzki8WGNT9RLl92dTsOFOjfNqN1Z2iliP0ei6jg_UC1_dcYmfrBc7vKkpulrUi-23kH9Rl-H8s0CYsSYtn9CFWkSigcY4jHWhOc-y7AHKSg9axCNoqe4HNIvPZa-QFA).
- Energy efficiency and facility retrofits: enterprise energy‑reduction initiatives and facility upgrades reported across sites (benchmarking, audits and retrofits cited in sustainability reporting) [businesswire](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQF-eXKeQwoTg3qTncBjKDfO94bAvP3A1G2SSaxIz7uQrXMNMHUBXzWEoDjPdUOAk_9qyHt84mebJZQCvNAfZGUmtE7mYnTOm4WYtQLRCJ1zHQmYPCuqUHy40tX9-5a900QjiVrEx8Fc5p1OmKuj1oyGVpm-gMXlLP5rhHNZCtb6qpB7h36pVpIc-OKrjeKg1FIsiJsGxpSVAsxPop3J6ZD6BHnoG4x1WCTf8g==) [responsibilityreports](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHg0bkQEw71u5Qhh3TZ8LmpZFRlFVwWKpUsTVX4TrSh-U4xAn8TiRL-Q_VmlV-BKgAbtdoRgKSMTH4Ztgzki8WGNT9RLl92dTsOFOjfNqN1Z2iliP0ei6jg_UC1_dcYmfrBc7vKkpulrUi-23kH9Rl-H8s0CYsSYtn9CFWkSigcY4jHWhOc-y7AHKSg9axCNoqe4HNIvPZa-QFA).
- Water reuse and process efficiency: “Operation Splashdown” (Palm Bay, FL) stormwater reuse project that reuses filtered stormwater for cooling and is projected to save ~20 million gallons of potable water annually; Greenville, TX parts‑fab water control retrofit that reduced freshwater usage in process tanks by ~70% and cut process wastewater/sludge by >50% at that site [l3harris](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFS--4QhvyuyeU2DFmZzsgpzHRdva_l17ddOpXQqOzhkTEXPnRRgtnKehMzKb3ZxD-QLGxUIFljo7mWCmWwPxPHIhSW5SncYG9SYRkC5WjY8buJy0FOckr2GhKn6-kRZLJCfwivV2WwqZFxywZ_gKw4itX1FvTaJFD7ioCNmxTio-ucdUm-jRwmz5JqqwSEEx_AoWP8xSXfBs06M-LGeFSprVBN6ucN-gs=) [youtube](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQG4h2Jst_xB-ldtatlCjJI1fc-nY6Lbrie-oyyPojblDSuSjJw0S7N-xxHOJisNTqXFbaTsGHcGdk4JPzwlto9--R7ff7heFs53gw9F_iblP8FMo8V4PE3N_UydNxQUT1AFfVc2eg==) [responsibilityreports](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHg0bkQEw71u5Qhh3TZ8LmpZFRlFVwWKpUsTVX4TrSh-U4xAn8TiRL-Q_VmlV-BKgAbtdoRgKSMTH4Ztgzki8WGNT9RLl92dTsOFOjfNqN1Z2iliP0ei6jg_UC1_dcYmfrBc7vKkpulrUi-23kH9Rl-H8s0CYsSYtn9CFWkSigcY4jHWhOc-y7AHKSg9axCNoqe4HNIvPZa-QFA).
- Waste diversion and materials: enterprise targets and programs to increase diversion (75% diversion target by 2026; 10% reduction in solid waste by 2030) and local recycling/diversion projects at facilities [responsibilityreports](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFY9oaGz3pROlbfaXumC0N5Klml9X2i8Lx0nijDrAajxG--T9h4izj6GWRBStm2lLAax8v5I_QauFwl24hmO375YcWnyNIFM8Tc0badvHLhXE66vban6KFt7Q0X-ehYscB2bbBjlupw58m9bKWAT4dwzKhr9bOtVtOpvm-XbzbuSKcUMS4WqzzhdMH0ec9t7ompjprgYK2K9vnRLQ==) [bwmonline](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEYObze8q2H6CBqtt-jUfbiDRd_xauA9hxaISUM5qGX86zl6iXAYBvwTJnutilnvC3EZfKdZ1c08rOonWNbza4Do3JrM9VqqUjbqwXhoLIuOWvd_R4X83J1Zi1OvEo0W-RaLnpXFtva1nKD1wDkY9iKn_pauGU1nHrCPws1j97LSMnodCaiz91ywPJTgaQkSeXbpPnkALdeI8K4EU4W_xQ91ZdIuYthvNwM9vizOk0BP1S2tDOdkNi5j2GZ).

Innovation Leadership (R&D, pilots, partnerships)
- Strategic partnerships and platform integration: Palantir partnership to integrate AI with L3Harris sensors and systems; venture partnerships (Shield Capital) to incorporate startup technologies; NOAA collaboration on advanced sensing (Advanced Baseline Imager) for environmental/meteorological monitoring (capability aligns to climate resilience and environmental sensing) [l3harris](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGf5atoVJsLdYaqI63UGp--c-YH45xg_TQMOuBzuCWvpZt1itWrWdMBGhBs-qWp_zn7R6e6Cr-k3GVD28gJIL9QebqjfamhwV9bGsmRVcw0XOX08KHwQdt4n35ofOz_rcQiMsETH_3tZODJq_VnIwoYIiSpBBWa0v7KMSHBhrBAY6vurlR8gOUbE7LnFqN9uqxZB0_OQrLf0A==) [responsibilityreports](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQETL8zW5s8Ix-azp7Tx4Z8eRZJ2MCC06hG2i70iaJeiFsyGTBNjfhyRfr-oh6Ce6zkWVLtX6bWTtPHgIOSXHrq5Mhemkij5g6TDvgF4H1iB_uSJg_lY1wRhzGD6Z6mH0xXtDNb-05pOxqa6BWsutd3seP0lNeNKtEuTiJmdv13kL1RQUkYfo4dBIABq6k92AIa0XFgUKryMLaUytg==) [l3harris](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHBeGcHFs8_dOOWt2Vp00t55J9fN6CWema8bGZxc_z2OrZmYEMPDi_A-nx2SVBBO3cNqbCCFPYdL22nOA5yaKFeWW9Yc6c0FNM9s9pb49Fxb1AEfva-3lUN_LRu8wFWIfzrNg4vvXg0).
- Corporate renewables and market innovation: VPPA approach (Lightsource bp) and multiple negotiated renewable projects are examples of strategic commercial innovation (using market mechanisms to drive decarbonization) [lightsourcebp](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQG9jVt-0UjBDO3tlVPj7Xnu73_r_4ouBGo5NOowdPnCQ40H658dG69oIci0e4FmPB8oFMyl1Kny2j34pHc0cnC8Kl84egu06pZ0n0MBows9S_HLyPZgslam1wRxCNR84FKuzM52yCu53pIxfY7R4p08VqtWQd4imglYfzlfx20A) [lightsourcebp](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHwF2WyXgyFMGRgCPo6thPu05ARCm58jeEqQ2l00SacIvqYEqYcTCjgv3H_X6OdLtK34uB69a2PWxBxyeVsaaTMikFXCkBBahQCVYdcNDCcj8nyqyyY90Uw6wMLgnnLjesO5LWFyYCqO91SbBFCKmfIhFV7gd2HjUaDTU2gtVIuuayt) [esgtoday](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFbcvVWFs-xlqjlF1i1Axw3meBw8OeVdCeDXn9IdSk5WXqJLIC8WSVanJr_K6VjQbfaAnDEHO1nYXSuST5P0vy2-aeSB8uwuTiQrEP1SO8mBwXpbFqpn8ng5p-x5vjNK0QelZBhBTjJkBJP7eIO9DPGeURwOmW0NJOLIZ_ToCcFp2c=).
- Patents & IP: L3Harris holds thousands of patents ( >3,000 engineers’ patents across the company) — however, most public patent references are in defense, communications, sensing and avionics rather than discrete “sustainable materials” or commercially‑focused green‑tech inventions; some IP relates to thermal management and related subsystems that can have sustainability co‑benefits [l3harris](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHMKdVqvEoCQFplRPua0RYmVUiaZoK-kFkkiG1gljhgcHaq_oITcgASXSEQ9AaV6ciXCC-yeO3pQHsG28gn70cSIP6ypFzT4kUAQCTxv9HX-h7a94MtbUiMI8sFJCrmWZGUyJAGXeXyzY1dQCHJb3gPAtBRaM4MFb3-dicqFz8k1zcCL6_0caP6oLs9ng==) [patentguru](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQExL7T_aC-ggUHoV3DaghBpx1Mv98BF9RlMPjj6j2iRmB7ur85eFNDvvPqo033LH4xscNhxfAhSt2Mgv8TX9hziLPiDOuXVIUAfRrTz2Ma9VJTriwpATRTLQKDv4tqs1f3cZCJ7IoMcwHWqIKrwqMqGN3oLiTL1kwVkQPpO) [justia](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFtQJzpVJKnbCOxQXMydZzIAY-dsMA7vJsmuDaBVMX3TZrBzWwLpbxvUObd7pMul_ajdJMCc83mvYFxdZaiTGmLrqn2igGJDKEB4lLJJk4A4MqjyPKA1E91zAboiKXbVJvXJT4xt7vOMfKz).
- Limitation: while L3Harris runs pilots/partnerships and applies engineering R&D to energy/water efficiency and environmental sensing, there is limited public evidence of large proprietary green‑technology product lines or breakthrough sustainable‑tech patents (most publicly disclosed R&D budget and patents focus on aerospace/defense product performance) [responsibilityreports](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQETL8zW5s8Ix-azp7Tx4Z8eRZJ2MCC06hG2i70iaJeiFsyGTBNjfhyRfr-oh6Ce6zkWVLtX6bWTtPHgIOSXHrq5Mhemkij5g6TDvgF4H1iB_uSJg_lY1wRhzGD6Z6mH0xXtDNb-05pOxqa6BWsutd3seP0lNeNKtEuTiJmdv13kL1RQUkYfo4dBIABq6k92AIa0XFgUKryMLaUytg==) [justia](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEzssqLeD351IM1BnVCmJNyKV6rPnJXatDqde8xEvpK2J_1nY5VBKLC2o0YiggRPt3uNIpxSpCfkqmJK3HZd4VEcrISTpQETsRekSzHASAKgAFGZewLHtSPuHGceQsTXw-_ANZf6PGCJ6E8GCqNxjRh_Yu2VsD9gzo=).

Measurable Impact (quantifiable results 2022–2025)
- Emissions metrics and progress: L3Harris reported total GHG emissions of ~212,058,000 kg CO2e in 2024 (≈212,058 metric tons: Scope 1 ~73,961 tCO2e; Scope 2 ~138,097 tCO2e); earlier reporting shows ~204,877,000 kg CO2e in 2023. The company exceeded an earlier 30% reduction target ahead of schedule and has reset ambitions to 60% reduction by 2030 (2021 baseline) [ditchcarbon](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGsp4oZy_yizG6mJPEn3B2u5a-hhW4bpLnaJ9b8UhHR3cNn5pf1cpgq7OjUBpf0wJR8ExqDBVfBVqWWF_wiAvx0g3KXqmLjWm5WPQS6UUH_CmCpIArw1ZBNAgT_WVpj41gCtzySxPLum6A=) [businesswire](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHTYtSVZyMZmYVCWFkEEkJbb0dumhM_FQuGiTo1I0uVykcFTuBMw1f_0Oe4Jc7ANOfEhMC23vyveNPMsORz8Wn4qFlU2ckzY5L96O-FH-zSwXnGARLu6s56k2Yu5loUgR73KEl6XbIYFkNYnrLzLwo7jJ8IoZKZhWgOD-ct75fVQHynb3UY-P3vfHcKXKZVqQcJwpbjolcT78VFlx0roLty) [smartenergydecisions](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQESb0VrEMN1bO-4Ehcczzatr9-anU-3yY2phm9rVYrRi6iULN--eXzlUnzhe1BLn5DQ-3L3wIxiYSqpuLlTvY92JnaxekB1fcloEXJZVieKmfeV76yZOn9kWuF6wns-93okyBXBTxi0X5Eb882hr8lSvN3xKYg8aPA9QVKobCBRUH_0YSEzsCNqQmdg0ALiRSW4CgpS).
- Renewable impact: Elm Branch VPPA estimated roughly 110,000 metric tons CO2e/year avoided — a material fraction of reported annual emissions and a major near‑term emissions abatement lever [lightsourcebp](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQG9jVt-0UjBDO3tlVPj7Xnu73_r_4ouBGo5NOowdPnCQ40H658dG69oIci0e4FmPB8oFMyl1Kny2j34pHc0cnC8Kl84egu06pZ0n0MBows9S_HLyPZgslam1wRxCNR84FKuzM52yCu53pIxfY7R4p08VqtWQd4imglYfzlfx20A) [esgtoday](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFbcvVWFs-xlqjlF1i1Axw3meBw8OeVdCeDXn9IdSk5WXqJLIC8WSVanJr_K6VjQbfaAnDEHO1nYXSuST5P0vy2-aeSB8uwuTiQrEP1SO8mBwXpbFqpn8ng5p-x5vjNK0QelZBhBTjJkBJP7eIO9DPGeURwOmW0NJOLIZ_ToCcFp2c=).
- Water savings: Operation Splashdown projected to save ~20 million gallons potable water annually; company reported a 43 megaliter reduction in annual water use in 2023 through site projects (condensate recovery, process improvements) [l3harris](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFS--4QhvyuyeU2DFmZzsgpzHRdva_l17ddOpXQqOzhkTEXPnRRgtnKehMzKb3ZxD-QLGxUIFljo7mWCmWwPxPHIhSW5SncYG9SYRkC5WjY8buJy0FOckr2GhKn6-kRZLJCfwivV2WwqZFxywZ_gKw4itX1FvTaJFD7ioCNmxTio-ucdUm-jRwmz5JqqwSEEx_AoWP8xSXfBs06M-LGeFSprVBN6ucN-gs=) [l3harris](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHHI-aFsm4cSVWMDS0OYwAxHVKv9yfhO4py5HfGE49nX9Fl2ZYUfg7e4r7neCvu8qEEgozuyjx7n7Hoxrc3pzrxsZ2lvhiCMY4dBhP89_mH_J5mk2t_6l-1UGpIrSqUN53SRzC8mqb2uI_O4lMGygfmApOKz0kPmT4luB5qSS-xjOd-ppxfxhiEFd8rOXA=).
- Facility‑level wins: Greenville TX parts‑fab: freshwater use down ~70% in the particular process; process wastewater and inorganic sludge reduced >50% at that facility after automation and control upgrades [youtube](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQG4h2Jst_xB-ldtatlCjJI1fc-nY6Lbrie-oyyPojblDSuSjJw0S7N-xxHOJisNTqXFbaTsGHcGdk4JPzwlto9--R7ff7heFs53gw9F_iblP8FMo8V4PE3N_UydNxQUT1AFfVc2eg==) [l3harris](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQH_36jhGaMHdE_B8-4-qwt0QJxca51Y9Odl0QXZoFLTqM7cza5iZzUwESRchzujXvmlEal5IFz-6zXnKz4ZbuH6Bmg9puDEG1zOhd5WlOiC3SbYhkpMTWqZwcY4SdYCKigwzLohkF-W0ffFYM4leql_6sWK0E-yiE4Cayjj1gcZ3gUbOgKasKosfSSPS0wI4jCbGzE1hDyUPxgHNDoHB2NbPzqCGPBeqJD0uX7SdpRD3BPsaQ==).
- Conclusion on measurable impact: L3Harris has measurable, documented operational improvements (energy via VPPA + on‑site solar, significant site water savings, waste diversion programs) that have produced company‑level emissions and resource reductions; however companywide absolute emissions remain material and further scaling and disclosure (scope 3, technology‑specific ROI) are still in progress [responsibilityreports](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFY9oaGz3pROlbfaXumC0N5Klml9X2i8Lx0nijDrAajxG--T9h4izj6GWRBStm2lLAax8v5I_QauFwl24hmO375YcWnyNIFM8Tc0badvHLhXE66vban6KFt7Q0X-ehYscB2bbBjlupw58m9bKWAT4dwzKhr9bOtVtOpvm-XbzbuSKcUMS4WqzzhdMH0ec9t7ompjprgYK2K9vnRLQ==) [esgnews](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGml6CGioNIfQpTi2UJGb_fGEW2Do7OFzHxlaIfBaGLaIqJ8P8svZpq5OVcUJ0s-nGVjt-E4-Twe9EsT6PeLVJ1-4Dpisvc5h7cW1CluYcCvgLpebqcuFf0rE8c8FUP_W0t75bc6eFbslRyjmKacpVkmNcoG7LgROuPslHmUU5J).

Future Strategy (commitments & roadmap)
- Clear near‑term targets with timelines: Reduce GHG emissions 60% by 2030 (2021 baseline); source 40% of electricity from renewable sources by 2030; reduce water use 20% and solid waste 10% by 2030; earlier 30% target was exceeded ahead of schedule [businesswire](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHTYtSVZyMZmYVCWFkEEkJbb0dumhM_FQuGiTo1I0uVykcFTuBMw1f_0Oe4Jc7ANOfEhMC23vyveNPMsORz8Wn4qFlU2ckzY5L96O-FH-zSwXnGARLu6s56k2Yu5loUgR73KEl6XbIYFkNYnrLzLwo7jJ8IoZKZhWgOD-ct75fVQHynb3UY-P3vfHcKXKZVqQcJwpbjolcT78VFlx0roLty) [smartenergydecisions](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHMD6992iwMV_xYSgYu0Mw9SmNXDuLaZGMxkXZdnUmkiPlsRgpcPz2L_-__K-7ZH9bpOQJ-RplX-WcUwtLDAZruEU2YE8Z067p6ImhmSEK-sPFbyVkwUN5A3DnNtVe3D2xnhoRCqMl337hr7NkwHjofY0rZhakGUI4pYR-AnSO5SWTqdA_t2Ms4z4B_JgA9uHwU4DMp) [bwmonline](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEYObze8q2H6CBqtt-jUfbiDRd_xauA9hxaISUM5qGX86zl6iXAYBvwTJnutilnvC3EZfKdZ1c08rOonWNbza4Do3JrM9VqqUjbqwXhoLIuOWvd_R4X83J1Zi1OvEo0W-RaLnpXFtva1nKD1wDkY9iKn_pauGU1nHrCPws1j97LSMnodCaiz91ywPJTgaQkSeXbpPnkALdeI8K4EU4W_xQ91ZdIuYthvNwM9vizOk0BP1S2tDOdkNi5j2GZ).
